-- Salaries in Australia Poised to Rise Amid Tight Labor Market, Review Says
-- B y   J a m e s   P a t o n
-- 2010-09-21T21:27:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/salaries-in-australia-poised-to-rise-amid-tight-labor-market-review-says.html
Australian salaries are set to rise
4 percent this year, with some “white-collar” jobs paying as
much as 25 percent more because of a tighter labor
market, the Australian Financial Review said, citing recruiters.  Financial services workers currently are receiving pay
raises of as much as 10 percent, the newspaper said, citing
Robert Half. Salaries are set to increase 4 percent this
financial year, the Review reported, citing Mercer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
